<p>&nbsp;</p> 
<p>&nbsp;</p> 
<h3 class="bonfire">Elden Ring&nbsp;Loretta's Mastery Guide</h3> 
<ul> 
 <li><a class="wiki_link" title="Elden Ring Loretta's Sorceries" href="/Loretta's+Sorceries">Loretta's Sorcery</a></li> 
 <li>Stamina Cost:&nbsp;33</li> 
 <li>Deals&nbsp;magic damage</li> 
 <li>When shooting at locked-on enemies or body parts close to the ground, the lower arrow generated has a tendency to hit the ground, reducing the potential damage output. It is recommended to either aim at a body part located higher up, or shoot from a higher elevation such as on horseback.</li> 
 <li><span style="color: #ff6600;"><em>NOTE:</em></span> Since <a class="wiki_link" title="Elden Ring Patch Notes" href="/Patch+Notes">Patch 1.07</a> FP Consumption has been Decreased from&nbsp;43 to 39.</li> 
</ul> 
<p>&nbsp;</p> 
<h3 class="bonfire">Elden Ring Loretta's Mastery Notes &amp; Tips</h3> 
<ul> 
 <li>This spell cannot be boosted by <a class="wiki_link" title="Elden Ring Arrow's Sting Talisman" href="/Arrow's+Sting+Talisman">Arrow's Sting Talisman</a></li> 
 <li>When fully charged, this spell is affected by <a class="wiki_link" title="Elden Ring Godfrey Icon" href="/Godfrey+Icon">Godfrey Icon</a>.</li> 
 <li>The spell does no bonus damage from charging unless unless fully charged.</li> 
 <li>If fully charged, it does roughly 22% more damage.</li> 
 <li>Updated to patch&nbsp;<strong>1.07</strong>. See&nbsp;<a class="wiki_link" title="Elden Ring Patch Notes" href="/Patch+Notes" target="">Patch Notes</a>&nbsp;for details.</li> 
</ul> 
<p>&nbsp;</p> 
