				<li id="16760463" class="cmnt-root" data="3" data-d="1661140901000"><ul class="comments"><li class="comment-box"><div class="avatar"><img src="/images/avatar.png" alt="" /><div class="comment-username">Anonymous</div></div><div class="comment"><div class="title"><span class="txt-subject"></span><input style="display: none;" class="txt-subject-ed"><span class="right cmt-ui"><a href="https://fextralife.com/forums/t579426/Loretta's-Mastery" rel="nofollow" target="_blank">22 Aug 2022 00:01</a>&nbsp;&nbsp;<a class="report-post" href="https://fextralife.com/forums/report.php?f=193&p=16760463" rel="nofollow" target="_blank" title="report this post"><span class="glyphicon glyphicon-flag" aria-hidden="true"></span></a></span></div><p class="txt-comment">with the proper invasion setup, you can one-shot pretty much anyone. best invasion spots that i&apos;ve found:<br/>the farum azula area right after godskin duo all the way to the great bridge is the absolute best place in the game to snipe people. so much open space and verticality. there are dozens of sneaky sniping spots and huge, open gauntlets that hosts have to run through.<br/>miquella&apos;s haligtree canopy. wide open space, plenty of spots to shoot from. there&apos;s one spot on a ledge that requires a jump over the void to get to that covers pretty much the whole area.<br/>leyndell is amazing if you can get on the rooftops.<br/>any swamp area. the area after the big underground rot lake is pretty fun.<br/>caves are actually kinda nutty. most of them have an open area with a ledge up top to snipe from. you can also catch hosts off guard around a corner.<br/>any place with a ladder is also good.<br/>camping elevators is kinda viable. make sure ur the one on top tho.<br/>some tips:<br/>make sure to aim away from people as it&apos;s harder to dodge that way (and the arrow tracking looks cool)<br/>use godfrey icon to increase damage of fully charged arrows.<br/>charge your arrows just over the edge of a platform to ensure that all four arrows hit.<br/>cosplay as sellen for maximum fashion souls.<br/>RL 125, 15 Vigor, 99 Int, around an 80% invasion win rate, and 100% fun</p><textarea style="display: none;" class="txt-comment-ed"></textarea><div class="clearfix"><a role="button" data-toggle="collapse" href="#zz-16760463" class="cmt-reply pull-right" href=""><span class="glyphicon glyphicon-share-alt"></span>Reply</a><a id="btnExpandComment" role="button" data-toggle="collapse" href="#replies-16760463" class="cmt-reply pull-right" href=""><span class="glyphicon glyphicon-share-alt"></span>Replies (<span class="replies">0</span>)</a><div class="vote pull-right"><section class="t-up"><span></span><p>6</p><i class="add">+1</i></section><section class="t-down"><span></span><p>3</p><i class="sub">-1</i></section></div></div><div class="collapse-com transparent"><div class="col-trigger collapse" id="zz-16760463"><div class="ng-scope"><textarea id="dcomment" class="ng-pristine ng-untouched ng-invalid ng-invalid-required" placeholder="Input your comments:"></textarea><button id="btn-16760463" class="btn btn-default btnPostReply"><i class="glyphicon glyphicon-pencil"></i> Submit</button><img id="newCommentAvatar" src="/images/avatar.png"/></div></div></div></div><div class="clearfix"></div><ul class="children collapse" id="replies-16760463"></ul></li></ul></li>
			
