				<li id="16590755" class="cmnt-root" data="17" data-d="1649064457000"><ul class="comments"><li class="comment-box"><div class="avatar"><img src="/images/avatar.png" alt="" /><div class="comment-username">Anonymous</div></div><div class="comment"><div class="title"><span class="txt-subject"></span><input style="display: none;" class="txt-subject-ed"><span class="right cmt-ui"><a href="https://fextralife.com/forums/t579426/Loretta's-Mastery" rel="nofollow" target="_blank">04 Apr 2022 05:27</a>&nbsp;&nbsp;<a class="report-post" href="https://fextralife.com/forums/report.php?f=193&p=16590755" rel="nofollow" target="_blank" title="report this post"><span class="glyphicon glyphicon-flag" aria-hidden="true"></span></a></span></div><p class="txt-comment">Adding onto my previous comment on how it’s meant to be used on horseback, it does do more damage, but is it worth the fp? It costs 1.5x more than Loretta’s Greatbow, so it should do 1.5x more damage, right? It seems to. I did testing on the Caravan Trolls outside of Sellen’s shop. Loretta’s Greatbow damage consistently did 966 damage, sometimes 1k-1.2k depending on how high up the arrow high(troll hitboxes). Loretta’s Mastery did 1,510 damage extremely consistently with two cases of it doing more and less damage. One time an arrow missed and it did roughly 1200 damage. Another time I somehow got 1900 damage and I was shooting the chest, not the head of the troll. <br/><br/><br/>So? 1,510 divided by 966 is a 1.56x multiplier roughly. I’m using Azur’s Glinstone Staff +9 and I have 75 intelligence and 22 Strength. This spell is definitely worth it on horseback against dragons and similar horseback bosses if you want to save time. 1.53x Cost for 1.56x damage ROUGHLY. More testing can be done by others. Remember, this spell is meant to be used on horseback, not on the ground, roleplay as Loretta for all I care if if helps justify it lol</p><textarea style="display: none;" class="txt-comment-ed"></textarea><div class="clearfix"><a role="button" data-toggle="collapse" href="#zz-16590755" class="cmt-reply pull-right" href=""><span class="glyphicon glyphicon-share-alt"></span>Reply</a><a id="btnExpandComment" role="button" data-toggle="collapse" href="#replies-16590755" class="cmt-reply pull-right" href=""><span class="glyphicon glyphicon-share-alt"></span>Replies (<span class="replies">1</span>)</a><div class="vote pull-right"><section class="t-up"><span></span><p>19</p><i class="add">+1</i></section><section class="t-down"><span></span><p>2</p><i class="sub">-1</i></section></div></div><div class="collapse-com transparent"><div class="col-trigger collapse" id="zz-16590755"><div class="ng-scope"><textarea id="dcomment" class="ng-pristine ng-untouched ng-invalid ng-invalid-required" placeholder="Input your comments:"></textarea><button id="btn-16590755" class="btn btn-default btnPostReply"><i class="glyphicon glyphicon-pencil"></i> Submit</button><img id="newCommentAvatar" src="/images/avatar.png"/></div></div></div></div><div class="clearfix"></div><ul class="children collapse" id="replies-16590755"></ul></li></ul></li>
			
				<li id="16590718" class="cmnt-root" data="9" data-d="1649062711000"><ul class="comments"><li class="comment-box"><div class="avatar"><img src="/images/avatar.png" alt="" /><div class="comment-username">Anonymous</div></div><div class="comment"><div class="title"><span class="txt-subject"></span><input style="display: none;" class="txt-subject-ed"><span class="right cmt-ui"><a href="https://fextralife.com/forums/t579426/Loretta's-Mastery" rel="nofollow" target="_blank">04 Apr 2022 04:58</a>&nbsp;&nbsp;<a class="report-post" href="https://fextralife.com/forums/report.php?f=193&p=16590718" rel="nofollow" target="_blank" title="report this post"><span class="glyphicon glyphicon-flag" aria-hidden="true"></span></a></span></div><p class="txt-comment">For those who don’t understand why the arrows hit the ground, I understand why now. It’s because it’s meant to be used while on horseback, just like Loretta. After testing this with a few dragons and night’s cavalry, I have to say it’s pretty reliable and looks damn cool. Greatbow for general use but this is definitely fun for horseback, even if the damage change isn’t noticeable considering it’s 4x as many arrows. Still not the best of an “upgrade” spell.</p><textarea style="display: none;" class="txt-comment-ed"></textarea><div class="clearfix"><a role="button" data-toggle="collapse" href="#zz-16590718" class="cmt-reply pull-right" href=""><span class="glyphicon glyphicon-share-alt"></span>Reply</a><a id="btnExpandComment" role="button" data-toggle="collapse" href="#replies-16590718" class="cmt-reply pull-right" href=""><span class="glyphicon glyphicon-share-alt"></span>Replies (<span class="replies">0</span>)</a><div class="vote pull-right"><section class="t-up"><span></span><p>9</p><i class="add">+1</i></section><section class="t-down"><span></span><p>0</p><i class="sub">-1</i></section></div></div><div class="collapse-com transparent"><div class="col-trigger collapse" id="zz-16590718"><div class="ng-scope"><textarea 